  "texts": [
    "In total, we surface and analyze six red-teaming exercises based on retrieved public reports.",
    "See Table 2 for more information.",
    "FindingsVariation in goals, processes, and threat models.",
    "Reflecting the lack of consensus on a definition of red-teaming in the literature, red-teaming activities frequently varied in form and in goals.",
    "Some organizations chose to conduct a single round of red-teaming [57,109,8,30], while others saw red-teaming as an iterative process in which results from initial rounds of testing were used to prioritize risk areas for further investigation [4,150,99]."
  ]
}